<li id="cite_note-Tiendis_2001-39">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Tiendis_2001_39-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Tiendis_2001_39-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Tiedens LZ, <i>Anger and advancement versus sadness and subjugation: the effect of negative emotion expressions on social status conferral</i>, Link: <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=11195894&amp;dopt=Citation" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=11195894&amp;dopt=Citation" rel="nofollow">[1]</a>, Journal of Personality &amp; <a href="/wiki/Social_psychology" title="Social psychology">Social Psychology</a>, 2001 Jan; 80(1):86-94.</li>
